1 Loading packages

requiredPackages = c('tidyverse', 'scales', 'fmsb', 'viridis')

for(p in requiredPackages){
  if(!require(p,character.only = TRUE)) install.packages(p, dependencies = TRUE)
  library(p,character.only = TRUE)
}

2 create_beautiful_radarchart function

#borrowed from: https://www.datanovia.com/en/blog/beautiful-radar-chart-in-r-using-fmsb-and-ggplot-packages/
create_beautiful_radarchart <- function(data, color = "#00AFBB", 
                                        vlabels = colnames(data), vlcex = 0.7,
                                        caxislabels = NULL, title = NULL, ...){
  radarchart(
    data, axistype = 1,
    # Customize the polygon
    pcol = color, pfcol = scales::alpha(color, 0.5), plwd = 2, plty = 1,
    # Customize the grid
    cglcol = "grey", cglty = 1, cglwd = 0.8,
    # Customize the axis
    axislabcol = "grey", 
    # Variable labels
    vlcex = vlcex, vlabels = vlabels,
    caxislabels = caxislabels, title = title, ...
  )
}

3 Variable Importance Scores

3.1 Reading dataset

dfAll <- read_csv("varImpShort.csv")
dfAll <- dfAll %>% 
  mutate(correlate = factor(correlate),
         domain = factor(domain, levels = c("Prosody", "VQ", "Cognitive")),
         Comparison = factor(Comparison, 
                             levels = c("Five groups", "Non-CD vs CD", "Clinical", "HC vs SCD", "HC vs naMCI", "HC vs aMCI", "HC vs pAD", "SCD vs naMCI", "SCD vs aMCI", "SCD vs pAD", "naMCI vs aMCI", "naMCI vs pAD", "aMCI vs pAD")),
         Grouping = factor(Grouping, levels = c("Prosody", "VQ", "Prosody Cog", "VQ Cog", "Prosody VQ", "Prosody VQ Cog")))
dfAll <- dfAll %>% 
  select(Grouping, Comparison, domain, 
         correlate, importance, pvalue) %>% 
  arrange(Grouping, Comparison, domain, desc(importance))
dfAll

4 Prosody

4.1 P value <= 0.1

4.1.1 Subset and manipulation

dfAll_Pros <- dfAll %>%  
  filter(Grouping == "Prosody") %>% 
  select(-c(Grouping, domain, pvalue)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(id_cols = Comparison,
              names_from = "correlate",
              values_from = "importance") %>% 
  replace(is.na(.), 0) %>% 
  mutate(Comparison = as.character(Comparison)) %>% 
  rbind(c("Max", rep(0.02, 16))) %>% 
  rbind(c("Min", rep(0, 16))) %>% 
  mutate(Comparison = factor(Comparison, 
                      levels = c("Max", "Min", 
                                 "Five groups",
                                 "Non-CD vs CD",
                                 "HC vs SCD", 
                                 "HC vs naMCI",
                                 "HC vs aMCI",
                                 "HC vs pAD",
                                 "SCD vs naMCI",
                                 "SCD vs aMCI",
                                 "SCD vs pAD",
                                 "naMCI vs pAD"))) %>% 
  slice(c(n(), 1:(n()-1))) %>% 
  slice(c(n(), 1:(n()-1))) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric) %>% 
  column_to_rownames("Comparison")

4.1.2 Plots

4.1.2.1 Per group

# Define colors and titles
colors <- viridis(dim(dfAll_Pros)[1]-2)
titles <- rownames(dfAll_Pros)[-c(1:2)]

# Reduce plot margin using par()
op <- par(mar = c(1, 1, 1, 1))
par(mfrow = c(4,3))

# Create the radar chart
for(i in 1:(dim(dfAll_Pros)[1]-2)){
  create_beautiful_radarchart(
    data = dfAll_Pros[c(1, 2, i+2), ], caxislabels = c(0, 0.005, 0.01, 0.015, 0.02),
    color = colors[i], title = titles[i]
  )
}
par(op)

4.1.2.2 Compared to average

dfAll_Pros2 <- dfAll_Pros[-c(1,2),]
dfAll_Pros2
df_scaled <- round(apply(dfAll_Pros2, 1, scales::rescale), 2)
df_scaled <- as.data.frame(df_scaled)
head(df_scaled)

# Variables summary
# Get the minimum and the max of every column  
col_max <- (rep(1, dim(dfAll_Pros2)[2]))
col_min <- (rep(0, dim(dfAll_Pros2)[2]))
# Calculate the average profile 
col_mean <- apply(df_scaled, 1, mean)
# Put together the summary of columns
col_summary <- t(data.frame(Max = col_max, Min = col_min, Average = col_mean))


# Bind variables summary to the data
df_scaled2 <- as.data.frame(rbind(col_summary, t(df_scaled)))
head(df_scaled2)



opar <- par()

par(mfrow = c(4,3))
# Produce a radar-chart for each student

  radarchart(
    df_scaled2[c(1:3, i), ],
    pfcol = c("#99999980",NA),
    pcol= c(NA,2), plty = 1, plwd = 2,
    title = row.names(df_scaled2)[i]
  )
}
